## Lesson Learned
1. Amazon Translate handles large docs better with .txt vs .docx formatting
2. Custom terminology: With Custom Terminology, you can override the standard neural machine translation by uploading CSV, TSV,  or TMX files. 
3. Brevity: If you need a shortened translation to define a product description or label without losing your core message, enable this setting.
4. Formality: This feature lets you set the tone of your text. You can use formal or informal language depending on your audience: professional, business casual, or friendly interaction. 
5. Profanity masking: If you want a safety feature to prevent profanity, make sure it is enabled.
6. Batch jobs in Amazon Translate are asynchronous, long-running operations that translate large volumes of text or documents (up to 5 GB per job) stored in Amazon S3, rather than providing real-time translation.
7. Always add human review - AI misses idioms and context.
